<p><a name="Ethics" id="Ethics"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Ecological_economics&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Ethics">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Ethics</span></h2>
<p>Mainstream economics has attempted to become a value-free 'hard science', but ecological economists argue that value-free economics is generally not realistic. Ecological economics is more willing to entertain alternative conceptions of utility, efficiency, and cost-benefits such as positional analysis or multi-criteria analysis. Ecological economics is typically viewed as economics for sustainable development,<sup id="cite_ref-10" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-10" title=""><span>[</span>11<span>]</span></a></sup> and may have goals similar to <a href="/wiki/Green_politics" title="Green politics">green politics</a>.</p>
<table class="infobox" style="font-size:95%; text-align:center">
